The paper deals with the problem of quickest change detection in a multisensor setting, which involves statistical inference and decision-making. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the mathematical foundations of information processing, including statistical inference. The paper also involves modeling a change process as a Markov process, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of Bayesian methods and dynamic programming suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). Finally, the paper deals with signal processing and detection, which falls under the category of cs.SP (Signal Processing).
